  "mixStrategy": "This relaxation Latin/Salsa arrangement uses the Andalusian cadence (Dm \u2192 C \u2192 Bb \u2192 A7) cycling every ~8 beats (~7.87s per cycle), giving us approximately 5.7 cycles over 45 seconds. The arrangement locks to a gentle son clave feel but in a spacious, floating way.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- BASS (Electric Bass, 100-300Hz, MIDI 33-48): Plays a gentle tumbao pattern \u2014 syncopated root notes with anticipated downbeats. Sits in the sub-bass/bass zone providing harmonic foundation. Roots: D(38), C(36), Bb(34), A(33).\n- CHORDS (Piano, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Montuno-inspired arpeggiated voicings in mid register. Gentle broken chords that outline the harmony. Sparse and floating \u2014 not the typical aggressive montuno, but rhythmically hinting at it with anticipations on the 'and' of beat 4.\n- MELODY (Flute, 1kHz-8kHz, MIDI 65-81): Lyrical, singing phrases in the upper register. Plays chord tones on strong beats (1 and 3), with scalar passages and ornamental turns on weak beats. Call-and-response phrasing \u2014 plays a phrase, then rests to breathe.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Bass anticipates beat 1 by an eighth note (clave feel). Piano montuno gently fills between bass hits. Flute melody floats above with longer, sustained phrases punctuated by short syncopated ornaments. All three lock to the same chord changes simultaneously.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments of ~7.5s each):\n- 0-7.5s: 0.3 energy \u2014 Bass and piano enter softly, melody hints\n- 7.5-15s: 0.5 \u2014 Melody enters with first full phrase, bass establishes tumbao\n- 15-22.5s: 0.6 \u2014 All voices active, gentle interplay\n- 22.5-30s: 0.7 \u2014 Peak energy, melody at highest range, fuller chords\n- 30-37.5s: 0.6 \u2014 Gentle pullback, melody becomes reflective\n- 37.5-45s: 0.4 \u2014 Fade, sparse notes, peaceful resolution\n\nCHORD CHANGES (each cycle ~7.87s, 8 beats at 61 BPM):\nDm (2 beats) \u2192 C (2 beats) \u2192 Bb (2 beats) \u2192 A7 (2 beats)\nTimes per cycle: beat1=0, beat3=1.97s, beat5=3.93s, beat7=5.9s",
